The paper deals with visual question answering (VQA), which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel regularization scheme for VQA, which involves adversarial training and language biases, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions using a question-only model to estimate the increase in model confidence after considering the image, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
